	Get rid of the silly gnu::access attribute. It might, for instance,
	break plugins written by people not having support for the
	attribute. And it adds nothing, because the Pratt parser itself
	treats the argument differently for the two different types of
	handler: it initializes the argument to NULL before calling a
	nud_handler_t.

	I made a few other minor changes.
	[f37639892fe5]

